<subSubSection pageId="48" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="48.[684,1213,1000,1488]" pageId="48">
ETYMOLOGY: From 
<emphasis box="[933,998,1364,1388]" italics="true" pageId="48">calvus</emphasis>
(L., “naked, bare”), in reference to the virtual lack of setae on the head and body, and - 
<emphasis box="[857,905,1431,1454]" italics="true" pageId="48">peza</emphasis>
, a common suffix in genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[712,849,1463,1487]" class="Insecta" family="Platypezidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Platypezidae</taxonomicName>
. The genus name is feminine.
</paragraph>
